        "discriminators": [
          "A mixed-material crash: one hard initial impact, then a shedding debris tail of many small bright inharmonic events (glass, metal, splinters). Front-loaded but NOT a single event — a low-ish temporal centroid combined with a very high transient_count is the signature.",
          "Against DESTRUCTION-COLLAPSE: a crash is faster, brighter and more front-loaded; a collapse is slower, heavier and LF-dominated with its energy spread through the file. Real but weak.",
          "Against EXPLOSIONS-REAL: no blast, far less sub-200 Hz energy, and a debris TRAIN rather than a decaying shockwave tail.",
          "Per the UCS note this is for MIXED materials; a single-material crash belongs in GLASS-CRASH & DEBRIS, METAL-CRASH & DEBRIS or WOOD-CRASH & DEBRIS, which are acoustically identical to it. That is why it cannot rise above narrowable."
